{
  "texts": [
    "In virtue of the attribution of distinct human characteristics that misrepresent and exaggerate AI capabilities and performance, anthropomorphism in AI can be viewed as a constitutive part of hype.",
    "To see this, consider first anthropomorphic language.Anthropomorphic language is so prevalent in the discipline that it seems inescapable.",
    "Perhaps part of the reason is because anthropomorphism is built, analytically, into the very concept of AI.",
    "The name of the field alone-artificial intelligence-conjures expectations by attributing a human characteristic-intelligence-to a non-living, non-human entity, which thereby exposes underlying assumptions about the capabilities of AI systems.",
    "Using such anthropomorphic language also invites interpreting algorithmic behavior as human-like so that it may be compared to human modes of reasoning [9].Going beyond the concept, there are many examples of anthropomorphic language that exaggerate the capabilities of AI, starting from the earliest days of the field."
  ]
}